my rent is $4,000 pcm
your rent is $2,500 pcm
the difference?
every unit i rent makes me $4,346 in profit every month
Here's how..

I don't rent places to lice
I rent places I can list on AirBNB to create passive income
- find a good area on data.rabbu
- use Zillow to pick a rental                   https://www.zillow.com/
- sign a corporate lease (3-5 yrs)
- add some amenities
- list it on airbnb
- optimize and book +85%
- collect the profit

Step 1: Start an LLC
you can do this for free with your state.
after 10 days, you will receive your business paperwork
you will go to IRS.gov and apply for an EIN number
This will let you open a business bank account and get credit

Step 2: Get a 0% credit line
if you have a 600+ credit score, you can start your business using other people's money
go to Chase, American Express, or BOA and take out a %0 interest loan
$20k should be enough to cover your rent, deposit, and furnishing costs

Step 3: Find a hot market
I only operate  in submarkets with +65% occupancy and I outcompete them
two good tools to find in-demand markets:
            data.rabbu (check seasonality)      https://data.rabbu.com/
            airbnb (confirm data)
            
market research, skills determine your profitability, learn well

Step 4: Pick a unit
go to Zillow, Realtor or Trulia and look for homes with nice amenities
make a spreadsheet with 50 units that profit most + the link to the listing
go down the list and set up an appointment to do a tour and pitch
(then follow up consistency)

Step 5: get it set up
once a landlord agrees to corporate lease, we need to make it feel like home
get some art, plants, and other unique amenities
use your business credit to pay the first month's rent/deposit 
then spend $10k-15k on high-quality furnishing

Step 6: Repeat the prcess
once i got this system working, i was addicted.
i wanted to do it over and over
each of my units profit 2-3x the monthly rent per month

rent: $4k
revenue: $9,5k
profit: $5k

in 2 years, able to scale to 14 units


